snippet: A ballot initiative that would have asked voters to split California into six states failed to qualify for the ballot in 2016, the secretary of state’s office said Friday.
abstract: Ballot initiative that would have asked voters to split California into six states fails to qualify for the ballot in 2016.
lead_paragraph: A ballot initiative that would have asked voters to split California into six states failed to qualify for the ballot in 2016, the secretary of state’s office said Friday.
